'''Maester Aemon''' is a recurring character in the [[Season 1|first]], [[Season 3|third]], [[Season 4|fourth]] and [[Season 5|fifth]] seasons. He is played by guest star [[Peter Vaughan]] and debuts in &quot;[[Lord Snow]].&quot;

Aemon is the [[maester]] at [[Castle Black]] and is one of Lord Commander [[Jeor Mormont]]'s closest advisers in the [[Night's Watch]].

He was born '''Aemon Targaryen''' and is the last [[House Targaryen|Targaryen]] in [[Westeros]]. He is the great-uncle of [[Daenerys Targaryen]], currently in exile in [[Essos]] and unaware of his existence. Aemon's origins have long been forgotten by most, as he has remained dedicated to his vows as a Maester and a brother of the Night's Watch for decades uncounted.Â

